  "text": "The next big result was due to Pǎtraşcu and Demaine [CITATION_1] , who managed to show an Ω(lg n) lower bound on the average cost per operation over a sequence of n updates and n queries to the partial sums problem. While matching the early results of Fredman, this bound also hold for weakly oblivious data structures.",
